1. PREFIX CACHING
Same prefix across requests
Best for: System prompts, few-shot examples
Savings: Significant token reduction
Impl: Most LLM APIs support natively

div.style: color: rgb(255, 255, 255) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;
div.span:
2. SEMANTIC CACHING
Similar queries
Best for: FAQ-style queries, repeated questions
Savings: 100% for cache hits
Impl: Embed query, search cache, return if similar

div.style: color: rgb(255, 255, 255) !important; display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;
div.span:
3. RESPONSE CACHING
Exact matches
Best for: Deterministic queries, idempotent ops
Savings: 100% for cache hits
Impl: Hash request, lookup, return cached response

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;
